    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="153"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d153">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Woodrow Wilson</persName> Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the Treasury</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_MWG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McAdoo</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName corresp="#p_WW1" type="to"
                            >Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-23">November 23,
                            1918</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. President</hi>: Here is a letter from your very
                    devoted admirer, Hon. <persName corresp="#p_MWG1">William McAdoo</persName>, of
                    New York.<note n="26" xml:id="d153fn26">Letter of Nov. 21, 1918 (not printed),
                        suggesting the appointment of <persName>Elihu Root</persName> to the
                        Commission to Negotiate Peace.</note> I pass it along to you for what it may
                    be worth. Unless your mind is already made up, it seems to me that on the whole
                    Mr. <persName>Root</persName> is well worth considering. I know the
                    disadvantages, but, on the other hand, the personnel of the commission as a
                    whole might outweigh these disadvantages.</p>
                <p>Affectionately yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">W. G. McAdoo</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
